│ has `EdgeIdx == UINT_MAX`, the current tree entry (`TE`) must be either:    │
│ (1) at index 0, (2) an extractelement instruction, (3) a splat (all same    │
│ values), or (4) have all scalars matching an existing tree entry with the   │
│ same main operation.\n\n2. **Analyzing `opt`'s Log**: From the debug log,   │
│ we can see that the SLP vectorizer is attempting to vectorize a complex     │
│ pattern involving PHI nodes and loads from a global array. The crash occurs │
│ when analyzing a tree entry with `Idx = 7` (not 0), which contains 4        │
│ different load instructions (`li.i.i.i`, `l2.i.i.i.i`, `l6.i.i.i.i`,        │
│ `l1.i.i.i.i`). This entry is not a splat (the values are different), not an │
│ extractelement (it's a load with opcode 32, not extractelement), and        │
│ doesn't match the expected conditions.\n\n3. **Root Cause Analysis**: The   │
│ issue stems from the fact that the assertion assumes that only certain      │
│ types of nodes can be children of gather nodes with `EdgeIdx == UINT_MAX`.  │
│ However, in this reproducer, we have a gather pattern where a PHI node      │
│ bundle references multiple different load instructions, creating a tree     │
│ entry that doesn't meet any of the expected conditions. The PHI nodes are   │
│ creating a complex dependency structure that results in a non-splat,        │
│ non-extractelement node being processed in this context, which violates the │
│ assertion's assumptions.\n\n4. **Proposed Edit Point(s)**: The assertion at │
