│ assertion should be removed or replaced with a conditional check that       │
│ returns early without crashing.\n\n5. **Conclusion**: By removing the       │
│ overly restrictive assertion, the SLP vectorizer will be able to handle     │
│ this edge case gracefully instead of crashing. The function already has the │
│ correct fallback behavior (returning an empty vector) immediately after the │
│ assertion, so removing the assertion will allow normal execution to         │
│ continue without the crash."})                                              │
