  "reason_thou": "1. **Understanding the Issue**: The SLP vectorizer is
crashing with an assertion failure in `isGatherShuffledEntry()`. The assertion
expects that when processing a gather node with a user that is also a gather
node and has `EdgeIdx == UINT_MAX`, the current tree entry (`TE`) must be
either: (1) at index 0, (2) an extractelement instruction, (3) a splat (all
same values), or (4) have all scalars matching an existing tree entry with the
same main operation.\n\n2. **Analyzing `opt`'s Log**: From the debug log, we
can see that the SLP vectorizer is attempting to vectorize a complex pattern
involving PHI nodes and loads from a global array. The crash occurs when
analyzing a tree entry with `Idx = 7` (not 0), which contains 4 different load
instructions (`li.i.i.i`, `l2.i.i.i.i`, `l6.i.i.i.i`, `l1.i.i.i.i`). This entry
is not a splat (the values are different), not an extractelement (it's a load
with opcode 32, not extractelement), and doesn't match the expected
