asserting and crashing, the function should handle this case gracefully by
returning an empty result (which is what it does immediately after the
assertion anyway). The assertion should be removed or replaced with a
conditional check that returns early without crashing.\n\n5. **Conclusion**: By
removing the overly restrictive assertion, the SLP vectorizer will be able to
handle this edge case gracefully instead of crashing. The function already has
the correct fallback behavior (returning an empty vector) immediately after the
